<title>HONG KONG: Kvaerner unit wins POSCO deal.</title>
<headline>Kvaerner unit wins POSCO deal.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-03-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>British-based metals and mining engineers Kvaerner Metals said on Wednesday it had been awarded an 18 million pound contract by South Korean steel giant POSCO to design, supply and supervise the erection of part of a blast furnace.</p>
<p>The contract covers bell-less top charging equipment, hot blast stoves, gas cleaning equipment and materials handling plant at POSCO's Kwangyang works.</p>
<p>Kvaerner Metals is a wholly owned subsidiary of Norway's Kvaerner ASA.</p>
<p>The furnace is scheduled to be in operation by March 1999 and will raise the overall iron-making capacity of POSCO's Kwangyang works by 2.8 million tonnes a year to 13.8 million tonnes, Kvaerner said.</p>
